When Wajahat passes away in an unexpected accident, Roshni‚Äôs estranged grandfather Hashmat Ali becomes her guardian. Advised by Safia, Wajahat‚Äôs sister who secretly resented her brother for her own failed marriage, Hashmat cancels Roshni‚Äôs upcoming marriage. Respectful of her grandfather and wanting to heal her family‚Äôs old differences, Roshni sacrifices her own choice once again and agrees to marry Umar, the son of the family‚Äôs munshi.  Instead of being embraced as a family member, things go from bad to worse for Roshni when she and her husband are treated extremely poorly by her spiteful aunt and her daughter Rania. Will Roshni continue to suffer at the hands of her own grandfather and aunt? Will Rayan, Roshni‚Äôs cousin  end up marrying Rania? Or will Roshni be able to get her life back on track somehow and overcome the obstacles that have been put in her path by her very own family?
